<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">404. Birren, Faber. Light, Color and Environment. 2nd rev. ed. West Chester, PA: Schiffer, 1988. 136 pp. Index, bibl. B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-88740-131-7. </p><p class="annot">This book is essentially a revised, expanded, and updated version ofsome of the information presented in Birrenâ€™s New Horizons of Color. It discusses the physical and psychological effects of color, with application to architecture and interiors and recommendations for color usage in homes, hospitals, schools, and other types of buildings. The revised edition includes a new eight-page chapter on facilities for computers. </p></div>
